  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preventing child recruitment into illegal armed conflict in Choc&#xF3;, Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.	Workshops with parents and teachers in the target communities sensitising them around children and young people&#x2019;s rights, vulnerabilities and how to keep them safe. 
2.	Assemblies with traditional and state authorities to discuss the situation and identify and implement concrete measures and policies to prevent child recruitment into armed forces and violence against children more generally.
3.	Youth &#x2018;camps&#x2019; where vulnerable children and young people will be empowered and educated to create a peaceful alternative to conflict and crime.
4.                  Visits to local schools and churches to ensure a high level of awareness of new policies and they will provide support to help communities ensure new child protection policies are applied.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This three year project seeks to build upon our partner Pastoral Social&#x2019;s success in reducing child recruitment into the conflict and improving children&#x2019;s safety and wellbeing more generally in the department of Choc&#xF3;.</narrative>
  </description>
